{
  "texts": [
    "However, if having many different implicitly elaborated definitions of constructs such as \"attitudes\", \"introjected regulation\", and \"resilience\" is in itself desirable in light of scientific progress, then what is the problem?",
    "The problem is the hidden nature of this heterogeneity.",
    "The exact (i.e.",
    "researcher-elaborated) definitions used in a given psychological study can vary considerably but typically remain unknown.",
    "Instead, reports of such studies tend to briefly (re)define the central constructs, or alternatively cite original formulations of the relevant theory."
  ]
}